data.jamchart_notes: Grippo adds beautifully to the Type I section of the jam. Out of the space, Spuds kicks into a funk groove and the band dives headfirst into a space highly reminiscent of Herbie Hancock. Rick and Grippo trade licks off each other like old friends while Peter saws away at grimy rhythm guitar. Builds in this zone for a while and is a must-hear piece of improv.

data.jamchart_notes: First "Creatures" jam ever with Peter on keys and he more than delivers. Steps up on Vintage Vibe and grooves along until Rick takes over in what will be the new standard jam for the song. Jam dissolves into rhythm-section-driven Ted space at the back end before landing smoothly in a perfectly-placed "Your Ocean." Absolute must-hear and a pivotal moment for the evolution of Goose jams.

data.jamchart_notes: Skips the final chorus for the first time ever and instead embarks on the jam from the space-out. Coalescing around Cotter's insistent play, the band builds a ferocious bliss vibe with an intensity found in very few Goose jams. You'll jump through the ceiling with the sheer force of this peak.

data.jamchart_notes: Makes the expected 2025 move into Goontz territory and beautifully rides that out for a while, but what isn't predictable is the 5.5-minute segue into "Hollywood Nights." No matter how early you hear this coming, it's remarkable to listen as each band member moves toward the Seger cover bit by bit, in zero hurry.

Moby was played for the first time since February 13, 2025 (58 shows). Before the show, creepy music played and technical difficulties ensued marked by Loomis calling over the PA, suddenly the entire crowd was sent through the veil much like the 4 lads from the promo video. Upon landing in a new world Barnaby Glimpse welcomed his new friends to his Show Upon Time. Following his opening monologue, the band kicked into a Menagerie set marked by animal balloons, animal puppets and animal performers. Carnies also passed out Goose branded Animal Crackers. After Animal, Barnaby reappeared on stage for a brief monologue. During the encore, members slowly left the stage, Cotter first after Jed, then Stu and Trevor after Master & a Hound. Peter left during Sugar Mountain. At the end of the song, Rick shut off the lamp on his rig and left the stage.
